@page "/"
@attribute [Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization.AllowAnonymous]

<PageTitle>CalCrony — events &amp; calendars for Discord</PageTitle>

<p class="meta-mono text-uppercase mb-2">Self-hosted · open source · for your Discord server</p>
<h1 class="display-6 fw-bold" style="letter-spacing:-.02em">
    Every event your server plans, in Discord <em class="text-primary fst-normal">and</em> in the browser.
</h1>
<p class="lead text-body-secondary" style="max-width:58ch">
    CalCrony is an event &amp; calendar bot with a real web app behind it. Create events in plain English,
    RSVP with one tap, get reminders, subscribe from any calendar app — and check the whole group's
    free/busy before you pick a time.
</p>

<div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 my-4">
    <a class="btn btn-primary"
       href="https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=1527749302443835532&permissions=8590019584&integration_type=0&scope=bot+applications.commands"
       target="_blank" rel="noopener">＋ Add CalCrony to your server</a>
    <a class="btn btn-outline-primary" href="/app">Open the app →</a>
    <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary" href="https://github.com/JJWren/CalCrony" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View source</a>
</div>

<div class="row g-3 mt-4">
    <div class="col-12 col-md-4">
        <div class="card h-100 p-3">
            <div class="fw-bold">Plain-English scheduling</div>
            <p class="text-body-secondary small mb-0 mt-1">"tomorrow 6pm", "friday at 8" — parsed in your timezone, DST-proof.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12 col-md-4">
        <div class="card h-100 p-3">
            <div class="fw-bold">Group availability</div>
            <p class="text-body-secondary small mb-0 mt-1">Link Google Calendar (free/busy only — never event details) and see who's actually free.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12 col-md-4">
        <div class="card h-100 p-3">
            <div class="fw-bold">Subscribe anywhere</div>
            <p class="text-body-secondary small mb-0 mt-1">Every server gets a calendar feed for Google, Apple, or Outlook.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h2 class="h5 mt-5 mb-3">One suite, two surfaces</h2>
<p class="text-body-secondary" style="max-width:66ch">
    RSVP from the browser and the Discord embed updates within seconds; RSVP in Discord and the web
    reflects it. Same events, same reminders, same calendar — wherever your people already are.
    The bot's <a href="/docs">command reference</a> covers everything Discord-side.
</p>
